gujarati.context:
Here is the translation:

He who has that nature, whoever sees it, will see it immediately; 
Another's virtue, duty, and spirit are his own fault, he will be seen.

Here is the translation:

The fourth chapter says Sukhroop Re, Form of Renunciation Anupo Re; 
That renunciation which becomes so, All means said are those of it.

Here is the translation:

In that way Hiri-gita was sung, mothers heard it and kept it in their hearts; 
Afterward mother spoke to her son, "My Lord God has spoken through my mouth."

Here is the translation:

A pleased face has been adorned with attire, a good Ambodha (or a pleasing sight) in the way; 
The moonlight is in harmony with the face, new lotus flowers stand upright.

Here is the translation:

The beauty of heaven is like a thread, the thread of the ratan is; 
The mulberry tree has withered in the hands of the moon god, the pot of the cobra god is seen.

Here is the translation:

Observe, joyous ones, that great men are attained, then they become Brahmin-like; 
Krishna, Hari, Hari, He is Krishna, thus I have seen my lord's form.

Here is the translation:

Melie eh deh uchhangare ra, rahya shraddhadhi dwadas sangare ra;
Durvasano shap te tulyo ra, morye hato tevo deh malyo ra.

Here is the translation:

Put your trust within, it will be good, plenty of notice will be; 
It has no care for human life, you should keep its account in mind.
